1
00:00:00,160 --> 00:00:01,460
(All characters, organizations,
and events in this drama are fictitious.)

2
00:00:01,460 --> 00:00:02,693
(Filming complied with guidelines
for children, youth, and animals.)

3
00:00:04,660 --> 00:00:06,060
That's who I am.

4
00:00:06,817 --> 00:00:08,817
Dong Pal. Jeong Dong Pal.

5
00:00:09,817 --> 00:00:12,350
Just prepare one big bill. Then I'll...

6
00:00:13,517 --> 00:00:16,817
keep my mouth shut forever
about your criminal record.

7
00:00:17,883 --> 00:00:19,050
Keep that mouth shut!

8
00:00:27,017 --> 00:00:27,550
(Chief Ko)

9
00:00:28,250 --> 00:00:29,750
Looks like you'd even kill someone.

10
00:00:31,617 --> 00:00:33,217
There's murder in your eyes.

11
00:00:34,417 --> 00:00:36,850
Then again, only the first time is hard.

12
00:00:37,917 --> 00:00:40,650
I guess it wouldn't be hard
since you've done it before.

13
00:00:45,250 --> 00:00:46,250
Three days from now,

14
00:00:47,417 --> 00:00:49,250
meet me here again at this time.

15
00:00:49,750 --> 00:00:51,017
If you don't show up,

16
00:00:52,417 --> 00:00:55,317
I'll march straight into Kangsu Group.

17
00:01:13,917 --> 00:01:14,917
Dad.

18
00:01:19,450 --> 00:01:22,217
Who told you to steal
Team Two's information?

19
00:01:24,250 --> 00:01:25,717
Did Manager Seo tell you?

20
00:01:25,850 --> 00:01:27,650
Just answer my question.

21
00:01:28,950 --> 00:01:31,717
Who told you to steal
Ms. Cho Eun Ae's files?

22
00:01:34,117 --> 00:01:35,117
I can never tell you.

23
00:01:36,250 --> 00:01:38,017
Even if a knife were at my throat,
I could never.

24
00:01:38,217 --> 00:01:39,217
Fine then.

25
00:01:40,517 --> 00:01:43,017
I'll take it to the disciplinary committee
before Manager Seo does.

26
00:01:44,417 --> 00:01:45,917
Chief, that's...

27
00:01:47,550 --> 00:01:49,017
If I get referred
to the disciplinary committee,

28
00:01:49,650 --> 00:01:52,717
this will spiral
completely out of control. Please.

29
00:01:53,517 --> 00:01:54,617
Spiral out of control?

30
00:01:57,317 --> 00:01:58,650
What exactly do you mean by that?

31
00:02:01,050 --> 00:02:04,617
More importantly, if that happens,
what will happen to our competition?

32
00:02:05,450 --> 00:02:06,450
Our team will...

33
00:02:06,650 --> 00:02:08,850
Are you seriously worried
about the competition right now?

34
00:02:11,417 --> 00:02:14,117
Go tell the person who put you up to this.

35
00:02:15,450 --> 00:02:17,017
If they interfere like this again,

36
00:02:17,750 --> 00:02:20,017
Team One will be
automatically disqualified from the race.

37
00:02:20,517 --> 00:02:23,817
Sorry? What do you mean by that?

38
00:02:25,217 --> 00:02:27,517
So our hunch was right after all.

39
00:02:28,617 --> 00:02:31,650
Your grandmother
was my maternal grandmother.

40
00:02:32,117 --> 00:02:34,150
I still can't believe it either.

41
00:02:36,017 --> 00:02:38,417
Wait. Then does that make us...

42
00:02:39,350 --> 00:02:40,350
Cousins?

43
00:02:43,450 --> 00:02:44,750
Does that make us what?

44
00:02:45,817 --> 00:02:46,817
Never mind.

45
00:02:47,517 --> 00:02:50,950
How is your grandma doing?
The shock must've been enormous.

46
00:02:51,817 --> 00:02:53,917
She collapsed from exhaustion
in front of the gate.

47
00:02:54,517 --> 00:02:56,117
She only managed to fall asleep
after taking a sleeping pill.

48
00:02:56,917 --> 00:02:58,617
I couldn't even say hello to her
before I left.

49
00:02:59,517 --> 00:03:00,517
My goodness.

50
00:03:01,217 --> 00:03:04,017
Then again, we're this shaken ourselves.

51
00:03:04,750 --> 00:03:06,217
What did the Chairman say?

52
00:03:06,317 --> 00:03:08,850
Grandpa says they should meet immediately,

53
00:03:09,517 --> 00:03:13,017
but Grandma wants to tell her herself,
so she asked for some time.

54
00:03:13,817 --> 00:03:15,650
For now, he says we should wait and see.

55
00:03:16,517 --> 00:03:20,117
What should we do?
Mom's resentment toward her runs so deep.

56
00:03:20,117 --> 00:03:21,817
I don't think she'll accept it easily.

57
00:03:22,517 --> 00:03:24,917
But we can't just sit back and do nothing.

58
00:03:25,517 --> 00:03:26,850
Before Grandma tells her,

59
00:03:27,050 --> 00:03:29,117
we should do whatever we can...

60
00:03:29,417 --> 00:03:30,717
to soften your mother's heart.

61
00:03:31,117 --> 00:03:32,417
Let's think of a way together.

62
00:03:32,650 --> 00:03:35,150
Okay. We should tell my dad, right?

63
00:03:35,717 --> 00:03:39,117
If Dad knows, he might be able
to persuade Mom at least a little.

64
00:03:39,317 --> 00:03:40,517
Yes, I think that's best.

65
00:03:41,817 --> 00:03:44,317
It's almost lunchtime.
Shall we eat with your dad?

66
00:03:44,550 --> 00:03:46,217
What? No.

67
00:03:46,550 --> 00:03:50,017
I'll just talk to Dad myself.
Enjoy your lunch.

68
00:03:57,317 --> 00:03:58,850
(Maternity Test Results, Results Report)

69
00:03:59,717 --> 00:04:00,950
What in the world...

70
00:04:01,250 --> 00:04:03,117
I still can't believe it
no matter how many times I look at it.

71
00:04:04,350 --> 00:04:06,917
Hold on. If this is true,

72
00:04:07,317 --> 00:04:09,450
doesn't that mean...

73
00:04:09,450 --> 00:04:11,717
Seong Jun gets a share too?

74
00:04:13,950 --> 00:04:17,150
I want to burn this thing to ashes!

75
00:04:17,917 --> 00:04:19,917
Wait!

76
00:04:22,450 --> 00:04:23,850
Come in.

77
00:04:30,317 --> 00:04:31,317
Have you finished approving everything?

78
00:04:32,250 --> 00:04:33,317
Approving?

79
00:04:34,517 --> 00:04:37,450
Why are there so many approval documents?

80
00:04:38,317 --> 00:04:40,117
You can take your time with the others,

81
00:04:40,517 --> 00:04:43,950
but the second competition budget
needs approval now.

82
00:04:44,617 --> 00:04:46,817
Hold on. Which one was it?

83
00:04:49,350 --> 00:04:50,617
Don't touch it!

84
00:04:51,517 --> 00:04:53,617
I'll find it myself. Don't touch anything.

85
00:04:54,617 --> 00:04:55,417
(Maternity Test Results)

86
00:04:57,617 --> 00:04:58,717
Get out!

87
00:04:59,017 --> 00:05:00,817
Stop touching my documents and get out!

88
00:05:00,817 --> 00:05:02,817
Hurry up. Out!

89
00:05:06,517 --> 00:05:08,417
Please call me
when you're done approving them.

90
00:05:16,317 --> 00:05:17,317
Did he see it?

91
00:05:18,517 --> 00:05:19,517
No, right?

92
00:05:20,417 --> 00:05:22,317
He couldn't have. No way he saw it.

93
00:05:34,750 --> 00:05:37,017
Maternity test results?

94
00:05:40,317 --> 00:05:43,717
What? Your hair? Why?

95
00:05:44,217 --> 00:05:46,150
If I knew, I wouldn't be so frustrated.

96
00:05:46,150 --> 00:05:49,217
I was so fed up
that I was going to confront her,

97
00:05:49,617 --> 00:05:51,350
but Sun Bun ended up ripping out...

98
00:05:51,350 --> 00:05:53,117
a fistful of her hair and chasing her off.

99
00:05:53,617 --> 00:05:55,450
I couldn't even say a word.

100
00:05:56,117 --> 00:05:59,650
A 99.9 percent match...

101
00:05:59,650 --> 00:06:01,317
No, not a match.

102
00:06:03,250 --> 00:06:04,250
Mr. Cho.

103
00:06:08,050 --> 00:06:09,850
What now? What's going on this time?

104
00:06:12,550 --> 00:06:13,550
No way.

105
00:06:17,517 --> 00:06:19,250
Hey. Where have you been?

106
00:06:26,317 --> 00:06:29,117
Something's going on, isn't it? Tell me.

107
00:06:29,750 --> 00:06:32,117
No, nothing's going on.

108
00:06:35,217 --> 00:06:36,217
Yes, Chairman.

109
00:06:37,050 --> 00:06:39,017
Yes, I'll come see you shortly.

110
00:06:41,517 --> 00:06:42,817
I'm heading to the Chairman's house.

111
00:06:44,017 --> 00:06:45,017
All right, go ahead.

112
00:06:55,417 --> 00:06:58,150
Hey, Eun Ae. Lunch?

113
00:06:58,717 --> 00:07:01,717
What? Mom is whose daughter?

114
00:07:02,717 --> 00:07:03,717
Is that true?

115
00:07:04,117 --> 00:07:08,017
Yes.
Grandma saw Mom's burn scar yesterday...

116
00:07:08,450 --> 00:07:10,117
and recognized her immediately.

117
00:07:11,750 --> 00:07:12,950
I can't believe this.

118
00:07:14,017 --> 00:07:17,517
I just can't believe it.

119
00:07:19,017 --> 00:07:21,350
Your mom probably has no idea.

120
00:07:21,617 --> 00:07:23,817
Dad, what do we do now?

121
00:07:24,517 --> 00:07:27,417
Mom won't even let anyone mention her mom.

122
00:07:28,917 --> 00:07:30,117
They still need to meet.

123
00:07:31,750 --> 00:07:33,617
As much as Mom hates her,

124
00:07:34,517 --> 00:07:36,217
she must miss her just as much.

125
00:07:36,817 --> 00:07:37,850
I know, right?

126
00:07:38,850 --> 00:07:42,717
Just look at how she's kept
Grandma's things all these years.

127
00:07:44,017 --> 00:07:45,450
I'll talk to Mom today.

128
00:07:46,017 --> 00:07:49,550
I'll try to soften her heart
a little first,

129
00:07:50,617 --> 00:07:52,450
then let Grandma tell her herself.

130
00:07:53,417 --> 00:07:55,717
- Eat up.
- Okay, Dad.

131
00:08:01,817 --> 00:08:03,917
What's wrong?
Something else bothering you?

132
00:08:04,717 --> 00:08:07,017
Dad, the thing is...

133
00:08:08,117 --> 00:08:11,317
If Team Manager's grandmother
is my grandmother too,

134
00:08:11,950 --> 00:08:13,417
then Team Manager and I...

135
00:08:15,750 --> 00:08:18,117
Yes, I understand how you feel.

136
00:08:19,317 --> 00:08:21,250
All the more reason to stay strong, okay?

137
00:08:23,217 --> 00:08:24,317
Okay, Dad.

138
00:08:24,817 --> 00:08:27,217
Let's eat. The soup's getting cold.

139
00:08:50,017 --> 00:08:51,017
Did you finish packing the lunchbox?

140
00:08:51,217 --> 00:08:53,950
Yeah. What made you want a packed lunch...

141
00:08:55,850 --> 00:08:57,017
- Who are you?
- What?

142
00:08:59,117 --> 00:09:01,017
Are you really my daughter Eun Nim?

143
00:09:02,450 --> 00:09:03,917
Why are you dolled up like this?

144
00:09:04,950 --> 00:09:06,717
Dolled up? What do you mean?

145
00:09:07,417 --> 00:09:08,917
You look pretty.

146
00:09:10,250 --> 00:09:12,017
I went through all that trouble
to birth pretty daughters,

147
00:09:12,017 --> 00:09:15,617
and both of them go around
in sweatpants looking like tomboys.

148
00:09:16,350 --> 00:09:18,250
You should dress like this more often.

149
00:09:18,250 --> 00:09:20,117
You can only enjoy dressing up
while you're young.

150
00:09:20,217 --> 00:09:21,917
I can't always go around
looking like this.

151
00:09:22,317 --> 00:09:24,517
I just felt like a little change for once.

152
00:09:26,017 --> 00:09:27,150
But why is there so little food?

153
00:09:28,450 --> 00:09:29,450
This is little?

154
00:09:29,817 --> 00:09:32,550
I packed three whole rolls.
Want me to add another?

155
00:09:32,750 --> 00:09:33,750
I'll do it.

156
00:09:45,850 --> 00:09:48,050
- I'm off.
- Okay.

157
00:09:52,717 --> 00:09:54,017
Did I make too much?

158
00:10:02,917 --> 00:10:05,417
Who could possibly eat only this much?

159
00:10:06,417 --> 00:10:09,850
What?
This is more than enough for a snack.

160
00:10:10,550 --> 00:10:12,817
Is there anything else besides sandwiches?

161
00:10:13,017 --> 00:10:15,017
To eat with that writer or whatever?

162
00:10:16,017 --> 00:10:18,817
You used to say snacks wouldn't fix things
between you two.

163
00:10:20,117 --> 00:10:21,517
Things are different these days.

164
00:10:22,017 --> 00:10:24,817
How should I put it?
She's prickly outside, soft inside.

165
00:10:25,750 --> 00:10:27,117
Prickly outside, soft inside?

166
00:10:27,117 --> 00:10:30,050
Yeah, prickly on the outside,
but soft on the inside.

167
00:10:31,950 --> 00:10:33,417
Something like that.

168
00:10:33,450 --> 00:10:35,417
Mark my words.

169
00:10:36,117 --> 00:10:40,017
No bowing and scraping
in front of that writer.

170
00:10:40,517 --> 00:10:43,017
Bowing and scraping? Me?

171
00:10:45,317 --> 00:10:46,650
Must run in the family.

172
00:10:46,917 --> 00:10:48,950
What? You little punk.

173
00:10:55,217 --> 00:10:56,217
I'm here, sir.

174
00:10:56,950 --> 00:10:58,917
Welcome.

175
00:11:00,117 --> 00:11:02,717
Mr. Seo, we found her.

176
00:11:04,017 --> 00:11:06,317
What do you mean?

177
00:11:08,650 --> 00:11:09,817
You found your daughter?

178
00:11:10,017 --> 00:11:13,817
Yes. She was right beside us all along.

179
00:11:14,717 --> 00:11:18,117
To think we failed to recognize her
right in front of us...

180
00:11:18,317 --> 00:11:21,350
and searched only in faraway places.

181
00:11:22,917 --> 00:11:23,917
Who is she?

182
00:11:25,617 --> 00:11:26,617
Hello.

183
00:11:29,717 --> 00:11:31,650
I came to see Ms. Yeong Hwa for a bit.

184
00:11:31,650 --> 00:11:34,717
Of course. Go on in.

185
00:11:35,050 --> 00:11:36,117
All right then.

186
00:11:43,317 --> 00:11:44,317
Chairman.

187
00:11:45,650 --> 00:11:46,750
It's her.

188
00:11:47,517 --> 00:11:49,250
Mr. Cho's wife.

189
00:11:49,250 --> 00:11:52,617
She's the Yeon Sun we've been
desperately searching for all this time.

190
00:11:53,417 --> 00:11:54,417
What?

191
00:11:59,017 --> 00:12:00,717
She still doesn't know yet.

192
00:12:01,450 --> 00:12:04,917
So much time has passed, and there are
many emotions that need sorting out.

193
00:12:05,450 --> 00:12:07,917
Please pretend you don't know for now.

194
00:12:10,617 --> 00:12:13,317
- Yes, sir.
- I should go inside.

195
00:12:14,650 --> 00:12:16,917
You've worked hard all this time.

196
00:12:17,117 --> 00:12:18,117
Not at all.

197
00:12:18,817 --> 00:12:19,850
Congratulations, Chairman.

198
00:12:31,817 --> 00:12:33,817
What brings you here, Kang Yeon Ja?

199
00:12:34,517 --> 00:12:35,850
A while ago, Ms. Yeong Hwa...

200
00:12:36,650 --> 00:12:39,517
I mean, Madam brought us some food,

201
00:12:40,017 --> 00:12:43,017
so I came to return the containers
and say hello.

202
00:12:43,117 --> 00:12:44,117
Is she inside?

203
00:12:44,117 --> 00:12:45,517
No, you can't.

204
00:12:45,950 --> 00:12:48,617
Mother isn't feeling well,
so just leave them there.

205
00:12:50,517 --> 00:12:53,017
I'll wake her up and let her know.

206
00:12:53,917 --> 00:12:55,417
Please wait here for a moment.

207
00:12:56,217 --> 00:12:57,550
No, sir.

208
00:12:57,550 --> 00:12:59,717
She doesn't seem well, so I'll just leave.

209
00:13:00,217 --> 00:13:03,417
Yes. Just go. Hurry along.

210
00:13:03,850 --> 00:13:06,817
Don't go. Wait just a moment.
I'll call her out soon.

211
00:13:08,050 --> 00:13:09,050
Father.

212
00:13:09,750 --> 00:13:11,550
This isn't
some kind of side-dish container relay.

213
00:13:11,750 --> 00:13:13,517
Why do you keep bringing things over?

214
00:13:14,717 --> 00:13:16,017
Who's here?

215
00:13:16,850 --> 00:13:19,717
My Yeon Sun? She's here?

216
00:13:21,317 --> 00:13:24,617
After all this time searching for her,
I guess the time has finally come.

217
00:13:25,817 --> 00:13:29,217
You two keep meeting,
as if drawn to each other.

218
00:13:30,017 --> 00:13:31,717
What do I do?

219
00:13:32,917 --> 00:13:36,717
I don't even know what to say
or where to begin.

220
00:13:38,117 --> 00:13:39,917
I feel like I'll just cry.

221
00:13:40,817 --> 00:13:42,650
You don't have to force it.

222
00:13:43,617 --> 00:13:44,717
She's your daughter.

223
00:13:45,750 --> 00:13:48,017
The Yeon Sun you've longed for
all this time.

224
00:13:49,850 --> 00:13:51,050
Okay.

225
00:13:51,717 --> 00:13:53,650
Should I get changed first?

226
00:13:54,117 --> 00:13:56,817
She's not going anywhere now.

227
00:13:57,717 --> 00:13:59,417
Don't rush and be calm.

228
00:14:00,250 --> 00:14:04,150
Take your time and give each other time
to open your hearts.

229
00:14:05,017 --> 00:14:06,817
You know what I mean, Yeong Hwa?

230
00:14:06,950 --> 00:14:10,450
Yes. I understand what you mean.

231
00:14:12,150 --> 00:14:14,250
Honey, it's an emergency.

232
00:14:14,717 --> 00:14:15,917
She's here again!

233
00:14:16,317 --> 00:14:18,117
Kang Yeon Ja came to our house again.

234
00:14:18,517 --> 00:14:20,250
She just went into Mother's room.

235
00:14:20,917 --> 00:14:24,217
What? What if they recognize each other?

236
00:14:25,917 --> 00:14:27,117
Listen to me carefully.

237
00:14:27,950 --> 00:14:30,617
Right now, bring them tea or some fruit,

238
00:14:30,617 --> 00:14:31,917
and sit right there with them.

239
00:14:33,250 --> 00:14:34,950
Don't let any nonsense come out.

240
00:14:34,950 --> 00:14:37,350
Plant yourself right in the middle...

241
00:14:38,050 --> 00:14:39,750
and keep a close watch on them.

242
00:14:39,917 --> 00:14:41,017
Me? Between the two of them?

243
00:14:41,717 --> 00:14:43,117
Honey.

244
00:14:43,117 --> 00:14:45,617
I can't control my facial expressions!

245
00:14:46,017 --> 00:14:49,217
They're mother and daughter.
How am I supposed to sit between them?

246
00:14:49,317 --> 00:14:52,950
Then are we just going to let
this powder keg explode?

247
00:14:53,717 --> 00:14:56,217
A powder keg? Okay, got it.

248
00:14:56,617 --> 00:14:58,717
I'll find a way to butt in somehow.

249
00:15:01,317 --> 00:15:03,617
What do I do? Should I wear this?

250
00:15:05,317 --> 00:15:06,417
No, not this.

251
00:15:06,617 --> 00:15:07,650
What do I do?

252
00:15:10,617 --> 00:15:13,117
Are you feeling unwell again?

253
00:15:14,017 --> 00:15:15,850
You look much thinner.

254
00:15:17,217 --> 00:15:18,450
Thinner?

255
00:15:19,750 --> 00:15:21,117
I'm fine.

256
00:15:23,117 --> 00:15:26,450
Is the Chairman in very bad condition?

257
00:15:27,117 --> 00:15:28,717
Yes, it is.

258
00:15:29,650 --> 00:15:33,317
That's why I'm... I'm sorry.

259
00:15:35,417 --> 00:15:36,517
My goodness.

260
00:15:38,317 --> 00:15:42,317
Even so, you need to stay strong.

261
00:15:43,517 --> 00:15:47,450
If you show tears like this,
the Chairman will only feel worse.

262
00:15:48,550 --> 00:15:51,950
Yeon Sun, it's me. Your mom.

263
00:15:52,450 --> 00:15:54,450
- My goodness.
- Yeon Sun!

264
00:15:55,617 --> 00:15:56,650
Ma'am, here...

265
00:16:02,317 --> 00:16:03,417
What can I do?

266
00:16:12,217 --> 00:16:13,217
Ma'am.

267
00:16:14,217 --> 00:16:15,517
Has the powder keg already exploded?

268
00:16:17,017 --> 00:16:19,450
Su Jeong, forget the tea.

269
00:16:19,917 --> 00:16:23,117
Sorry? But we have a guest.

270
00:16:23,450 --> 00:16:25,950
I said forget it.

271
00:16:25,950 --> 00:16:27,117
Ma'am.

272
00:16:27,517 --> 00:16:30,050
Go play golf, or go shopping.

273
00:16:30,617 --> 00:16:31,617
Don't just stay at home all day.

274
00:16:31,617 --> 00:16:33,717
No, Father. The house is a powder keg...

275
00:16:34,417 --> 00:16:37,217
I mean, Mother is bedridden right now.

276
00:16:37,217 --> 00:16:41,050
Hurry. Take that back to the kitchen,

277
00:16:42,117 --> 00:16:43,217
and go to your room.

278
00:16:43,417 --> 00:16:44,417
What?

279
00:16:45,617 --> 00:16:46,617
Okay.

280
00:16:55,017 --> 00:16:57,717
I don't even know what to say
to comfort you.

281
00:16:59,550 --> 00:17:01,517
Whenever I'm having a hard time,

282
00:17:02,317 --> 00:17:04,417
you're the one who comforts me
and gives me strength.

283
00:17:05,317 --> 00:17:07,350
What strength
could I have possibly given you?

284
00:17:08,017 --> 00:17:10,117
Of course you did.

285
00:17:11,350 --> 00:17:13,017
Whenever my mind was troubled,

286
00:17:13,917 --> 00:17:16,017
you always listened to me.

287
00:17:17,417 --> 00:17:20,117
Right. I enjoyed the flower pancakes.

288
00:17:22,117 --> 00:17:24,750
You ate my flower pancakes?

289
00:17:26,650 --> 00:17:29,417
Actually, I didn't. My family did.

290
00:17:30,550 --> 00:17:32,650
- What?
- I can't eat flower pancakes.

291
00:17:32,950 --> 00:17:36,417
Why not?

292
00:17:40,250 --> 00:17:41,450
When I was little,

293
00:17:42,650 --> 00:17:44,650
they were my favorite food in the world.

294
00:17:46,017 --> 00:17:49,817
But after the person who made them
for me abandoned me,

295
00:17:50,117 --> 00:17:51,350
I couldn't eat them anymore.

296
00:17:55,517 --> 00:17:56,917
That person was my mother.

297
00:18:00,217 --> 00:18:01,417
When I was seven,

298
00:18:02,817 --> 00:18:05,917
she abandoned me, chasing a better life.

299
00:18:08,450 --> 00:18:10,817
The truth is, my mother isn't dead.

300
00:18:13,417 --> 00:18:15,750
I have no way of knowing
whether she's dead or alive.

301
00:18:17,117 --> 00:18:19,650
She's just dead in my heart.

302
00:18:21,550 --> 00:18:26,117
And after that? How did you grow up...

303
00:18:27,617 --> 00:18:29,417
after your mother left you?

304
00:18:32,550 --> 00:18:34,717
The restaurant owner who took me in...

305
00:18:36,350 --> 00:18:37,950
left me at an orphanage,

306
00:18:39,217 --> 00:18:41,917
and the following year,
I was sent to France to be adopted.

307
00:18:43,017 --> 00:18:44,317
I couldn't even speak the language,

308
00:18:45,517 --> 00:18:47,617
and they didn't like that I had a scar.

309
00:18:50,017 --> 00:18:53,650
Actually,
I suffered severe burns as a child,

310
00:18:53,850 --> 00:18:56,017
so I have a large scar on my leg.

311
00:18:57,417 --> 00:19:01,050
Five years later, the adoption
was annulled, and I returned to Korea.

312
00:19:02,350 --> 00:19:06,117
After that, I lived in an orphanage
the whole time.

313
00:19:10,817 --> 00:19:12,950
Ma'am, I don't think this is a good idea.

314
00:19:12,950 --> 00:19:14,450
I should get going...

315
00:19:17,617 --> 00:19:18,817
I want to hear more.

316
00:19:19,417 --> 00:19:21,717
Tell me the rest of the story too.

317
00:19:23,250 --> 00:19:24,250
What?

318
00:20:06,950 --> 00:20:09,317
Hello, Bung Nim.

319
00:20:10,417 --> 00:20:12,717
Hello, Bung Wu.

320
00:20:19,217 --> 00:20:21,050
That's an awful lot of gimbap...

321
00:20:22,317 --> 00:20:23,717
for someone who looks like
they live on air.

322
00:20:24,817 --> 00:20:28,050
My mom's gimbap is amazing.

323
00:20:28,617 --> 00:20:29,717
Want to try some?

324
00:20:32,017 --> 00:20:33,017
Sure.

325
00:20:37,917 --> 00:20:41,617
With your hair like that,
you look really cu...

326
00:20:42,850 --> 00:20:43,850
Just a second.

327
00:20:50,617 --> 00:20:51,617
Hello, Hye Ji.

328
00:20:53,717 --> 00:20:54,717
Where?

329
00:20:58,917 --> 00:21:00,017
What's going on with you two?

330
00:21:00,017 --> 00:21:03,050
They're lunchboxes.
We each brought our own.

331
00:21:04,117 --> 00:21:05,350
Who said they weren't lunchboxes?

332
00:21:06,017 --> 00:21:08,317
I'm asking why there's so much food
for just two people.

333
00:21:08,317 --> 00:21:11,117
We're both bigger eaters than we look.

334
00:21:11,450 --> 00:21:13,517
Why don't you join us, Hye Ji?

335
00:21:13,517 --> 00:21:14,517
Shall I?

336
00:21:15,717 --> 00:21:16,717
Sure.

337
00:21:18,617 --> 00:21:21,917
But why the cake?
Is it someone's birthday today?

338
00:21:22,250 --> 00:21:24,917
What? You don't know what today is?

339
00:21:25,050 --> 00:21:26,050
What's today?

340
00:21:26,317 --> 00:21:28,317
It's our Two-Two Day.

341
00:21:28,650 --> 00:21:31,417
The 22nd day since we started dating.

342
00:21:33,517 --> 00:21:35,517
Two-Two what?

343
00:21:40,217 --> 00:21:41,417
I'm hurt, Mr. Seo.

344
00:21:41,850 --> 00:21:43,617
You forgot our Two-Two Day.

345
00:21:44,117 --> 00:21:46,350
Come on.

346
00:21:46,717 --> 00:21:48,417
I can't even remember Day One.

347
00:21:48,950 --> 00:21:50,917
What's this Two-Two Day nonsense?

348
00:21:51,650 --> 00:21:52,650
I'm leaving.

349
00:21:53,650 --> 00:21:55,317
You two enjoy your lunch date...

350
00:21:55,817 --> 00:21:56,717
and your Two-Two Day party.

351
00:21:57,517 --> 00:21:58,517
No.

352
00:21:58,617 --> 00:22:00,917
At least finish your lunch before you go.

353
00:22:01,117 --> 00:22:02,217
You've only had one bite.

354
00:22:02,217 --> 00:22:03,217
Why do you care?

355
00:22:04,050 --> 00:22:06,150
Hye Ji, enjoy your meal and the party.

356
00:22:06,617 --> 00:22:07,617
In that case...

357
00:22:08,517 --> 00:22:09,517
Then I'll go too.

358
00:22:10,217 --> 00:22:13,417
I forgot I needed to change
Bung Wu and Bung Nim's tank water.

359
00:22:15,617 --> 00:22:16,617
What's with you two?

360
00:22:18,317 --> 00:22:20,417
Are you flirting?

361
00:22:20,617 --> 00:22:22,017
- Flirting?
- Flirting?

362
00:22:35,117 --> 00:22:37,317
There's only one week left
until the second round.

363
00:22:37,417 --> 00:22:39,017
Shouldn't we start working late again?

364
00:22:39,450 --> 00:22:42,450
Working late? We might have to
before the final rehearsal.

365
00:22:43,317 --> 00:22:44,717
I don't see why we'd need to.

366
00:22:45,317 --> 00:22:46,817
We can just do online meetings
if necessary.

367
00:22:47,550 --> 00:22:50,450
Sure. Just let me know
whenever you need to do an online meeting.

368
00:22:50,850 --> 00:22:52,417
I'll be on standby at all times too.

369
00:22:53,750 --> 00:22:56,050
Thanks, everyone.

370
00:23:03,617 --> 00:23:05,817
Get a grip, Cho Eun Ae.

371
00:23:06,217 --> 00:23:08,550
Your mom just found her mother
after 50 years.

372
00:23:09,317 --> 00:23:10,917
What are you worrying about right now?

373
00:23:11,717 --> 00:23:13,917
Our problem isn't even a problem.

374
00:23:21,017 --> 00:23:22,017
What's going on?

375
00:23:23,150 --> 00:23:25,017
Sorry? What do you mean?

376
00:23:27,650 --> 00:23:29,217
Why are you looking at me like that?

377
00:23:30,017 --> 00:23:31,217
Let's just have the meeting.

378
00:23:38,950 --> 00:23:39,950
Looks good.

379
00:23:40,017 --> 00:23:42,750
All right.
Please make sure you're fully prepared...

380
00:23:43,017 --> 00:23:44,517
for your assigned parts.

381
00:23:45,150 --> 00:23:47,217
Lucas wants a final meeting.

382
00:23:47,317 --> 00:23:49,250
Manager Seo, how's your schedule tonight?

383
00:23:52,217 --> 00:23:54,850
Just prepare one big bill. Then I'll...

384
00:23:56,250 --> 00:23:59,617
keep my mouth shut forever
about your criminal record.

385
00:24:00,650 --> 00:24:01,817
Keep that mouth shut!

386
00:24:07,117 --> 00:24:08,117
Manager Seo Seung Ri?

387
00:24:09,117 --> 00:24:10,117
Yes?

388
00:24:12,550 --> 00:24:15,017
Chief, something's come up.

389
00:24:15,217 --> 00:24:16,417
I'm going home.

390
00:24:28,017 --> 00:24:29,117
You're home already?

391
00:24:29,717 --> 00:24:32,550
I need to ask you something urgently.

392
00:24:33,817 --> 00:24:36,217
Where your dad was 25 years ago?

393
00:24:36,217 --> 00:24:38,050
After moving into the Chairman's annex,

394
00:24:38,950 --> 00:24:41,850
Dad wasn't home for almost five years.

395
00:24:41,850 --> 00:24:44,450
Come on. I told you already.

396
00:24:45,117 --> 00:24:48,717
He was in Poland setting up
Kangsu's Eastern European branch.

397
00:24:48,817 --> 00:24:51,417
Poland? Was he really in Poland?

398
00:24:52,517 --> 00:24:54,317
Even if he was assigned overseas,

399
00:24:55,050 --> 00:24:57,517
how could he not come home even once
during all that time?

400
00:24:57,617 --> 00:24:59,517
You're poking at old wounds again.

401
00:25:00,350 --> 00:25:01,917
That was when Dad's business collapsed,

402
00:25:02,417 --> 00:25:04,450
and our family was buried in debt.

403
00:25:05,217 --> 00:25:06,217
Don't you remember?

404
00:25:06,817 --> 00:25:09,450
The whole house was covered
in red seizure notices.

405
00:25:09,917 --> 00:25:13,117
Debt collectors camped out everywhere,

406
00:25:13,117 --> 00:25:14,617
smashing up the house.

407
00:25:15,017 --> 00:25:16,117
I vaguely remember.

408
00:25:17,217 --> 00:25:18,717
I was terrified back then.

409
00:25:20,317 --> 00:25:24,317
Then the Chairman paid off all our debt
and even gave us the annex.

410
00:25:25,150 --> 00:25:27,717
How could your dad not be loyal
to the company after that?

411
00:25:28,517 --> 00:25:31,317
He was sent to the newly established
Eastern European branch...

412
00:25:31,817 --> 00:25:34,017
and worked day and night before returning.

413
00:25:35,450 --> 00:25:36,850
That's when his abilities were recognized,

414
00:25:37,650 --> 00:25:40,517
and he joined the Chairman's office.

415
00:25:43,117 --> 00:25:44,117
Why are you asking?

416
00:25:44,617 --> 00:25:46,617
Why all these questions
about 25 years ago?

417
00:25:46,917 --> 00:25:49,317
No reason. I just got curious.

418
00:25:49,850 --> 00:25:53,817
Mom, give me the number
of that guy from the company cafe.

419
00:25:54,117 --> 00:25:57,317
Why? Don't tell me
you're planning to meet him.

420
00:25:57,317 --> 00:25:59,817
No, nothing like that. Just give it to me.

421
00:26:08,550 --> 00:26:12,217
That guy gave me a bad feeling.
It's probably nothing serious, right?

422
00:26:13,717 --> 00:26:15,250
Mom, I need to get back to the office.

423
00:26:15,450 --> 00:26:16,717
The second round is coming up,
and I'm busy.

424
00:26:17,217 --> 00:26:18,217
See you.

425
00:26:20,150 --> 00:26:24,050
If you're that busy,
why did you come all the way here?

426
00:26:29,317 --> 00:26:30,317
Shall we call it a day?

427
00:26:30,917 --> 00:26:32,617
No. You go ahead.

428
00:26:32,617 --> 00:26:33,917
I'm staying to finish my work.

429
00:26:35,917 --> 00:26:37,817
Come outside for a minute.
Get some fresh air.

430
00:26:38,617 --> 00:26:40,217
No thanks. I don't have time for that.

431
00:26:42,350 --> 00:26:44,917
Ms. Cho Eun Ae, let's talk.

432
00:26:45,750 --> 00:26:46,750
I have something to say.

433
00:26:54,617 --> 00:26:55,617
Why are you avoiding me?

434
00:26:56,217 --> 00:26:59,117
What? No, I'm not.

435
00:27:00,617 --> 00:27:02,250
You wouldn't even look me
in the eye all day.

436
00:27:02,417 --> 00:27:05,117
You wouldn't have lunch with me
or leave work with me.

437
00:27:06,450 --> 00:27:08,750
There aren't many stars out tonight.

438
00:27:09,850 --> 00:27:11,017
Maybe it's the lights.

439
00:27:11,417 --> 00:27:14,250
Want me to guess what's been on your mind?

440
00:27:17,050 --> 00:27:18,050
Here.

441
00:27:19,017 --> 00:27:20,117
What's this?

442
00:27:20,250 --> 00:27:21,950
You said you wanted to see
what I looked like as a kid.

443
00:27:23,417 --> 00:27:26,517
This is the only photo I have of myself
at age seven.

444
00:27:29,050 --> 00:27:30,717
This was taken on your birthday,
wasn't it?

445
00:27:32,517 --> 00:27:33,617
And this person...

446
00:27:34,850 --> 00:27:37,217
He's the one...

447
00:27:37,217 --> 00:27:39,117
in the photo on your desk, right?

448
00:27:39,617 --> 00:27:41,617
That's right. He's my father.

449
00:27:42,517 --> 00:27:43,517
On that day 25 years ago,

450
00:27:44,617 --> 00:27:47,217
the day I first met little Eun Ae
at the playground,

451
00:27:48,050 --> 00:27:49,717
this man told me
we had a birthday party to go to.

452
00:27:50,250 --> 00:27:52,250
Gyeol, Han Gyeol.

453
00:27:53,617 --> 00:27:56,217
My biological father, Han Su Cheol.

454
00:27:57,417 --> 00:27:58,417
Team Manager.

455
00:27:59,017 --> 00:28:01,950
I'm adopted.

456
00:28:16,617 --> 00:28:18,550
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
